    Deal with changing index in a collection. The indexes are from 1 to ..., usually with a step of 1 between two items. There can be more than an increment of 1 between two items : it means there is one (or more) empty slot(s) between the items.

      • changeItemPosition

        public void changeItemPosition​(T itemToMove,
                               int newIndex,
                               Collection<T> collection)
        Set the new position of the item. If needed, initialize the indexes of the collection first to ensure that the indexes are unique inside the collection.

        If we move the item where there is already a card, all cards between the old and the new position are moved to let space.

        If we move the item to an empty slot, it is just a swap between the card and the empty place. No other card change.

        Parameters:
        itemToMove - the item to change
        newIndex - the new index to set
        collection - the collection of items
